        "@value": "inverse of the shortest duration of a signal element",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "The term \"modulation rate\" is used in conventional telegraphy and data transmission. In isochronous digital transmission, the term \"line digit rate\" is generally used.\n\nSee <<iec60050-704,locality:item=\"704-17-03\">>.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
