        "@value": "traffic intensity (<<t13-1,item 13-1>>) of the traffic served by a particular pool of resources",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "stem:[1 \" E\"] corresponds to the occupancy of one resource.\n\nGeneral practice is to estimate the traffic intensity as\nan average over a specified time interval, e.g. the\nbusy hour.\n\nSee <<iec60050-715,droploc%locality:item=\"715-05-04\">>.\n",
        "@language": "en"
