      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t13-9-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "storage capacity, storage size",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t13-9-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "M",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t13-9",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "13-9",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t13-9-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t13-9-0"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "amount of data that can be contained in a storage device, expressed as a number of specified data elements",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "For the unit one, see the <<intro>>.\n\nThe specified data elements depend on the\norganization of the storage device, for example,\nbinary elements (also called \"bits\"), octets (also\ncalled \"bytes\"), words of a given number of bits,\nblocks. A subscript referring to a specified data\nelement can be added to the symbol.\n\n[example]\nstorage capacity for bits, stem:[M_{\"bit\"}] +\nstorage capacity for octets, stem:[M_o] or stem:[M_B].\n\nFor registers, the term \"register length\" is used with\nthe same meaning.\n\nAlthough in this context the designation \"bit\", symbol\nbit, is not really a unit, it is often used like a unit, e.g.\nstem:[M_{\"bit\"} = 32000], where the unit one is implicit, is often\nwritten as stem:[M = 32000 \"unitsml(bit)\"]. Similarly, although the\ndesignation octet or byte, symbols o and B,\nrespectively, are not units, they are often used like\nunits, e.g., stem:[M_o = 4000] or stem:[M_B = 4000], where the unit\none is implicit, are often written stem:[M = 4000] o or\nstem:[M = 4000 \" B\"].\n\nWhen used to express a storage capacity or an\nequivalent binary storage capacity, the bit and the\noctet (or byte) may be combined with SI prefixes or\nprefixes for binary multiples.\n\nIn English, the name \"byte\", symbol B, is used as a\nsynonym for \"octet\". Here, \"byte\" means an eight-bit\nbyte. However, \"byte\" has been used for numbers of\nbits other than eight. To avoid the risk of confusion, it\nis strongly recommended that the name \"byte\" and\nthe symbol B be used only for eight-bit bytes.\n\nThe symbol B for byte is not international and is not\nto be confused with the symbol B for bel.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-1"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-bit"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-o"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-B"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-13"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t13-10-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "equivalent binary storage capacity",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t13-10-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "M_e",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t13-10",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "13-10",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t13-10-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t13-10-0"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "stem:[M_e = \"lb\"\\ n]\n\nwhere stem:[n] is the number of possible states\nof the given device\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "For the unit one, see the <<intro>>.\n\nThe minimum storage capacity of a bit-organized\nstorage device which would contain the amount of\ndata in the given storage device is equal to the\nsmallest integer greater than or equal to the\nequivalent binary storage capacity.\n\nWhen used to express a storage capacity or an\nequivalent binary storage capacity, the bit may be\ncombined with SI prefixes or prefixes for binary\nmultiples (see <<sec_4>>).\n\nIn this context, \"bit\" is a special name as well as\nsymbol for the coherent unit one. For the unit one,\nsee the <<intro>>.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-1"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-bit"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-13"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t13-11-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "transfer rate",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t13-11-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "r",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t13-11-1",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "(v)",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t13-11",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "13-11",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t13-11-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t13-11-0"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t13-11-1"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "quotient of the number of specified data elements transferred in a time interval by the duration of this interval",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "The symbol stem:[nu] is the Greek letter nu.\n\nA subscript referring to a specified data element can\nbe added to the symbol.\n\n[example]\ndigit rate, stem:[r_d] or stem:[nu_d] (see <<iec60050-702,droploc%locality:item=\"702-05-23\">> and\n<<iec60050-704,droploc%locality:item=\"704-16-06\">>); +\ntransfer rate for octets (or bytes), stem:[r_o, r_B, nu_o] or stem:[nu_B];\nbinary digit rate or bit rate (<<t13-13,item 13-13>>).\n\nIn English, the name \"byte\", symbol B, is used as a\nsynonym for \"octet\". Here \"byte\" means an eight-bit\nbyte. See remarks in <<t13-9,item 13-9>>.\n\nThe octet per second (or byte per second) may be\ncombined with prefixes, for example kilooctet per\nsecond, symbol ko/s (or kilobyte per second, symbol\nkB/s).\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-s^{-1}"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-o/s"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-B/s"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-13"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t13-12-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "period of data elements, period duration of data elements",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t13-12-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "T",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:symbol"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t13-12",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "13-12",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t13-12-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t13-12-0"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "stem:[T = 1 // r] where r is the transfer rate\n(<<t13-11,item 13-11>>) when the data elements are\ntransmitted in series\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "A subscript referring to a specified data element can\nbe added to the symbol.\n\n[example]\nperiod of digits, stem:[T_d]; +\nperiod of octets (or bytes), stem:[T_o] or stem:[T_B].\n\nFor the unit second, see <<iec60050-112,droploc%locality:item=\"112-02-04\">>.\n\nSee <<iec60050-171,droploc%locality:item=\"171-06-05\">>.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-s"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-13"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t13-13-0",
      "@type": [
        "smart:Term",
        "skosxl:Label"
      ],
      "skosxl:literalForm": {
        "@value": "binary digit rate, bit rate",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "smart:hasTermFormType": {
        "@id": "smart:fullForm"
      }
    },
